Harrismith police detectives have warned the local community to be aware of thieves stealing cash from people s bank accounts through ATM scams or fraud on debit cards. Apparently, four cases were reported by complainants in which cash was withdrawn from their accounts after allowing [themselves] to be helped at the ATM by strangers, Sergeant Mmako Mophiring said. They always realised only when the text message is send to their cellphones that money was withdrawn. So let us be aware and only seek help from the security or bank official employed by the bank. Always avoid getting help from strangers at any ATMs, Mophiring said. African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.